1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:11,000
The same correction returns in another session,
while rules and skills keep piling up.

2
00:00:11,000 --> 00:00:24,000
Accumulation is not improvement.
Useful paths should brighten; unused branches should fade.

3
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:36,000
That is Codex Metabolism:
selection, validation, and subtraction for collaboration.

4
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:49,000
Codex understands the work and authors the improvement.
The runtime remembers and constrains. The human decides.

5
00:00:49,000 --> 00:01:00,000
First, the runtime prepares bounded, ordered evidence.
It makes zero semantic decisions.

6
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:12,000
The active Codex Agent recognizes one workflow
across different commands and different corrections.

7
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:25,000
Before creating anything, it checks built-ins,
installed capabilities, this repository, and the ecosystem.

8
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:37,000
It reuses the repository preflight
and writes a complete deployment skill.

9
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:49,000
The proposal cites evidence, states uncertainty,
predicts an effect, and defines when to roll back.

10
00:01:49,000 --> 00:02:01,000
The runtime validates every reference and generates a digest.
Changing the proposal or artifact invalidates approval.

11
00:02:01,000 --> 00:02:13,000
The human approves that exact version before it becomes live.
The intervention contract returns in the next review.

12
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:24,000
Rollback archives the skill instead of deleting it.
Other layers keep their existing Git or platform rollback.

13
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:35,000
Later evidence is compared with the original success and withdrawal conditions.
Silence is not success.

14
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:40,000
Codex Metabolism.
The Agent thinks. The runtime remembers and constrains.
